    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is mitigated by the conservative nature of ASTM F1717 loading, the multi-laboratory experimental program, and the multi-code FEA ensemble, which collectively provide sufficient confidence that the FEA framework adequately predicts compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated pedicle screw construct for the intended regulatory submission.",
